content: AI latency hit 18%. The team's efforts are paying off, but we're not stopping until we reach that 20% mark.
Finalizing the neural interface prototype for real-world testing. We're integrating it with our AI trading algorithm next week.
Had a good laugh with friends over coffee. Talked about the absurdity of our dependency on tech. It's good to keep perspective.
Dr. Li's feedback on the policy paper was invaluable. We're now focusing on real-world case studies to solidify our points.
AI module now at 94% accuracy. The fine-tuning is making a difference. Can't wait for the trading simulation next week.
Took a tech-free subway ride again. Overheard an argument about the ethics of self-driving cars. Fuel for the policy paper.
Latency is at 18.5%. We're close to our goal, but the real challenge will be maintaining it in live trading scenarios.
Dr. Li and I reviewed the latest draft of our paper. It's shaping up well, but we need more robust data to back our claims.
Neural interface prototype now fully integrated with our trading system. Initial tests show a promising reduction in decision time.
Another tech-free day, this time a long walk in Brooklyn. My thoughts are clearer, and I've got some new angles for our paper.
AI latency now at 19%! We're just one percentage point away. The team's excitement is palpable.
Dr. Li and I are finalizing the policy paper for submission. Our focus on empathy in AI is now well-articulated and supported.
The AI trading algorithm simulation starts tomorrow. If it goes well, we'll be ready for real-world testing.
Tech-free day turned into an impromptu jam session with friends. Sometimes, the best ideas come when you're not looking for them.
